---

<section
  class="hero-section relative overflow-hidden"
  aria-label="Josef Anolin — Stand-Up Comedian"
>
  <h1 class="sr-only">
    Josef Anolin — Stand-Up Comedian
  </h1>

  <div class="hero-top">
    <div class="hero-comp">
      <img
        src="/joe-hero.png"
        alt=""
        aria-hidden="true"
        class="hero-portrait select-none pointer-events-none"
      />
      <img
        src="/joe-logo.png"
        alt="Josef Anolin — Stand Up Comedian"
        class="hero-logo select-none pointer-events-none"
      />
    </div>
    <a href="#contact" class="hero-cta">BOOK ME</a>
  </div>

  <p class="hero-bio">
    From Oakland, California currently living in Los Angeles, Josef has opened
    for the likes of Tom Segura, Whitney Cummings, and Michael Che. He likes
    telling irreverent stories based on his life and observations. He has an
    Android phone because he likes pissing you off with his green text bubbles.
  </p>
</section>

<style>
  .hero-section {
    background: #000;
    height: 100%;
    /* Targets: 200px from window-top to subject's hat, 250px guard at the
       bottom. Locked to those exact values at typical desktop heights
       (1080+); shrinks proportionally on shorter viewports. */
    padding-top: clamp(120px, 20dvh, 200px);
    padding-bottom: clamp(160px, 25dvh, 250px);
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    padding-right: 1.5rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    /* flex-start keeps comp+button+bio packed tight at the top — no
       flex distribution gap between elements. The 250px buffer becomes
       empty space at the bottom of the card. */
    justify-content: flex-start;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .hero-top {
    position: relative;
    width: min(85%, 900px);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: flex-start;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .hero-comp {
    position: relative;
    width: 100%;
    /* Aspect ratio chosen so the comp's bottom edge meets the bottom of
       the visible artwork (logo bottom). Tweak in concert with
       .hero-logo bottom/width if the layered images change. */
    aspect-ratio: 2.4 / 1;
  }

  .hero-portrait {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    right: 5%;
    /* Width chosen so portrait's hat sits at comp top and shoulders
       reach near comp bottom. */
    width: 40%;
    height: auto;
    z-index: 1;
  }

  .hero-logo {
    position: absolute;
    /* Anchor logo's bottom flush with comp bottom. With logo width 40%
       (~30% smaller than the 70% it had in the flat composite), logo
       height ≈ 27% of comp_w which ≈ 64% of comp_h, so the JOSEF/ANOLIN
       stack lands across the shoulder/chest area — clear of the face. */
    bottom: 0;
    left: 5%;
    width: 40%;
    height: auto;
    z-index: 2;
  }

  .hero-cta {
    /* Logo spans left:5% to 45% of comp width — its center is at 25%.
       margin-left:25% + translateX(-50%) anchors the button's center
       to the logo's center, so "BOOK ME" sits centered under the title. */
    margin-top: 1rem;
    margin-left: 25%;
    transform: translateX(-50%);
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    background: var(--color-accent);
    color: #000;
    font-family: var(--font-display), system-ui, sans-serif;
    font-size: 1rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    padding: 0.85rem 1.9rem;
    border-radius: 9999px;
    text-decoration: none;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    transition: filter 0.18s ease, transform 0.18s ease;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }
  .hero-cta:hover {
    filter: brightness(1.1);
    transform: translateX(-50%) translateY(-2px);
  }

  .hero-bio {
    max-width: 60ch;
    text-align: center;
    color: rgb(229 229 229);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .hero-section { padding-left: 1rem; padding-right: 1rem; }
    .hero-top { width: 92%; }
    .hero-bio { font-size: 0.85rem; }
  }
</style>
